---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const title = 'Advertiser Disclosure';
const description =
  'How ITINCreditScore.com makes money: affiliate links, partner referrals, and advertising. Our compensation never costs you anything or changes our editorial guidance.';
const updated = 'June 5, 2026';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/disclosure">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="tag">Legal</span>
      <h1 style="margin-top:10px">Advertiser Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="byline">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <p>
        {SITE.legalName} is an independent publisher operated by
        Timberline Ventures LLC ("we," "us," "our"). The guides, tools, and
        comparisons on this site are free to read because we earn money from a
        small number of advertising and affiliate relationships. This page
        explains exactly how we get paid, who pays us, and, most importantly,
        the firewall we keep between that money and what we tell you. It is
        written to comply with the U.S. Federal Trade Commission's
        <em>Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in
        Advertising</em> (16 CFR Part 255), which require any "material
        connection" between a publisher and a product it recommends to be
        disclosed clearly and conspicuously.
      </p>

      <h2>How we earn revenue</h2>
      <p>
        We have three revenue streams, and every page on this site is funded by
        one or more of them:
      </p>
      <ul class="lead-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Affiliate links through Commission Junction (CJ).</strong>
          Many of our outbound links to specific credit-building products,
          secured cards, and credit-builder loans, are affiliate links served
          through the Commission Junction (CJ Affiliate) network. When you click
          one of these links and then qualify, sign up, or open an account, the
          advertiser pays us a commission. The link carries a tracking code that
          tells CJ the referral came from us; it does not transmit your personal
          information to us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Affiliate display advertising through Awin.</strong> Some of
          the banner units on the site, including the Credit Karma unit you may
          see on certain pages, are served through the Awin affiliate network.
          We are paid when you click the unit and complete an action on the
          advertiser's site (for example, signing up for a free credit-score
          account). These units are always labeled "Advertisement."
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Display advertising through Google AdSense.</strong> On our
          educational articles we run contextual display ads served by Google
          AdSense and its partners. We are paid based on impressions and clicks.
          We do not control which specific advertiser appears in an AdSense slot,
          Google's system selects those, and their presence is not an
          endorsement by us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tools-matching referrals.</strong> When you use our
          tools-matching form, we may connect you with a third-party
          credit-building provider and be paid a referral fee if you proceed.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How compensation affects (and does not affect) what you read</h2>
      <p>
        This is the part that matters most. Being paid by an advertiser can
        influence <em>which</em> products we choose to write about and
        <em>where</em> on a page a product link appears. It does
        <strong>not</strong> change the facts we report, the trade-offs we
        disclose, or our assessment of whether a product is right for a given
        situation. We do not accept payment to change a recommendation, to remove
        a drawback from a comparison, or to call a weak product a strong one.
        Our editorial conclusions are reached before, and independently of, any
        commercial arrangement, and they would read exactly the same if we earned
        nothing from them.
      </p>

      <h2>How we select and rank products</h2>
      <p>
        Products and tools are chosen for coverage based on how relevant and
        accessible they are to ITIN holders, specifically whether a product
        accepts an ITIN in place of a Social Security Number, whether it reports
        to the three nationwide credit bureaus (Experian, Equifax, and
        TransUnion), its real costs and deposit requirements, and how suitable it
        is for someone building a thin or nonexistent credit file. A product is
        never included simply because it pays the highest commission, and a
        relevant product is never excluded simply because it pays us nothing or
        has no affiliate program at all. Where we compare options, the attributes
        in our tables (deposit amounts, bureau reporting, fees) reflect publicly
        documented product terms, which can change; we tell you to verify the
        current terms directly with the provider before you apply.
      </p>

      <h2>What this means for you</h2>
      <ul class="lead-list">
        <li>
          <strong>It is never a cost to you.</strong> Our compensation comes from
          advertisers and partners, not from you. You never pay more for a
          product because you reached it through one of our links, and the price
          and terms you get are the same as if you had gone to the provider
          directly.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We do not cover every option.</strong> This site does not
          include every credit-building product, lender, or provider in the
          market. Absence from our site is not a judgment about a product.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We are not the provider.</strong> All credit products are
          offered by third parties under their own terms, eligibility rules, and
          applicable law. Approval, rates, and features are set by the provider,
          not by us.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our editorial promise</h2>
      <p>
        Opinions, comparisons, and recommendations are our own. They are not
        provided, reviewed, approved, or endorsed by any advertiser, affiliate
        network, or partner. Our research process, how we source from primary
        materials and review guides for accuracy, is described on our
        <a href="/editorial-policy">editorial policy page</a>. We aim to give you
        accurate, useful information so you can make your own decision. If we ever
        get something wrong, <a href="/contact">tell us</a> and we will correct
        it.
      </p>

      <h2>Not financial advice</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on this site is financial, legal, tax, or immigration advice, and
        we are not a credit bureau, credit-repair organization, lender, bank, or
        financial advisor. We do not set your credit score, originate loans, or
        make credit decisions. Always confirm current rates, terms, and
        eligibility directly with the provider before you apply. See our
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a> and <a href="/privacy">Privacy
        Policy</a> for more.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
